Fill and boil your kettle. Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Pour a good glug of @oil{} onto a #baking tray{} (to completely cover the bottom) and pop in your oven. Pour the boiling water into a #large saucepan{} on high heat with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Peel the @potatoes{450%g}, chop them into 3cm chunks. Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook for ~{5-6%mins} or until the edges have softened when you poke them with a #knife{}. Meanwhile, peel the @garlic{2%cloves} and pop into #foil{} with a drizzle of oil and scrunch to enclose it.

While the potatoes cook, halve the @premium tomato mix{125%g} and pop them into a #bowl{} with half of the @red wine vinegar{24%ml}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}. Pour in the @olive oil{3%tbsp}(for the salsa). Add half the @walnuts{20%g}, mix together and set aside.

Once the potatoes are ready, drain in a #colander{}, pop back into the pan then sprinkle on the @plain flour{1%tbsp} and @dried oregano{1%tsp}. Give your pan a shake to fluff up the potato. Take your hot baking tray out of your oven, carefully transfer your potatoes onto it in a single layer, turning in the oil. Pop the garlic foil parcel onto the tray as well. Season the potatoes with salt, then roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{30-35%mins}, turning halfway through. Remove the garlic after ~{8-10%mins}.

Pop the @flat leaf parsley{}(a handful), @tarragon{1/2%tsp}, @Dijon mustard{10%g}, remaining @walnuts{20%g}, remaining @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the dressing) and @water{1%tbsp} into a #mini food processor{} and blend until smooth.

> TIP: If you don't have a blender, chop the ingredients as finely as you can and combine in a bowl.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Once cooked, add the roasted garlic to the mix and blend again.

Ten mins before the potatoes are cooked, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Season the @21 day aged British fillet steaks{2} on both sides with salt and pepper. When hot, add the steaks to the pan. Fry until they browned, ~{1-2%mins} on each side. Lower the heat to medium and cook the steaks for another ~{2-3%mins} on each side if you want them cooked to medium-rare. Add ~{1-2%mins} extra on each side if you like your steak medium or well done.

> IMPORTANT: The steak is safe to eat when the outside is browned. Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

When the steak is cooked, transfer to a #plate{}, cover loosely with foil and rest for a couple of minutes. While the steak rests, add the @pea shoots{40%g} to the tomatoes and dressing and toss to coat. Slice the steak in half diagonally. Slice the steak and serve with the potatoes and salad alongside. Spoon the salsa verde pesto over the steak and around the plate.